WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:29.960
There was forest all round.

00:29.960 --> 00:34.960
All round for hundreds of kilometers, and there were no roads in the forest.

00:34.960 --> 00:37.960
There were only tracks.

00:37.960 --> 00:39.960
Two tents stood in a clearing.

00:39.960 --> 00:42.960
Two men were standing near the tents.

00:42.960 --> 00:47.960
The younger man, Manuel, was making coffee on a small stove.

00:47.960 --> 00:49.960
He looked up at the sky.

00:49.960 --> 00:53.960
It's going to rain today, he said.

00:53.960 --> 00:58.960
I know, replied Leon, and the rain will turn the ground into mud.

00:58.960 --> 01:01.960
Then we'll never get back to base.

01:01.960 --> 01:04.960
Four men were working in the forest.

01:04.960 --> 01:07.960
They were looking for iron and other metals.

01:07.960 --> 01:13.960
Leon was the boss, and he was angry.

01:13.960 --> 01:15.960
It was early morning.

01:15.960 --> 01:21.960
Leon and Manuel were ready to leave, but Joe and Pedro were out in the forest.

01:21.960 --> 01:25.960
They left in the truck two days ago, said Leon.

01:25.960 --> 01:27.960
They're very late.

01:27.960 --> 01:30.960
Joe was always making trouble.

01:30.960 --> 01:33.960
He was younger than Leon, and he was clever.

01:33.960 --> 01:35.960
He wanted to be boss.

01:35.960 --> 01:41.960
Manuel poured the coffee into mugs, and the two men drank it slowly.

01:41.960 --> 01:44.960
Suddenly, they heard the sound of a truck.

01:44.960 --> 01:47.960
They're back, said Manuel.

01:47.960 --> 01:50.960
The truck came up the rough track.

01:50.960 --> 01:52.960
It stopped near the tents.

01:52.960 --> 01:55.960
Joe jumped out.

01:55.960 --> 01:58.960
He was a big man with red hair.

01:58.960 --> 02:00.960
He was smiling.

02:00.960 --> 02:03.960
His smile made Leon more angry.

02:03.960 --> 02:05.960
Your late, said Leon.

02:05.960 --> 02:07.960
Where have you been?

02:07.960 --> 02:12.960
Hunting, replied Joe, and he held up his rifle.

02:12.960 --> 02:15.960
Hunting, Leon shouted angrily.

02:15.960 --> 02:19.960
That's not your job. We haven't time for hunting.

02:19.960 --> 02:22.960
We were away for two days, replied Joe.

02:22.960 --> 02:24.960
We're not very late.

02:24.960 --> 02:28.960
I'm the boss here, Leon shouted.

02:28.960 --> 02:30.960
Joe looked at Leon angrily.

02:30.960 --> 02:33.960
He was not smiling now.

02:33.960 --> 02:36.960
We're late. Very late, said Leon.

02:36.960 --> 02:40.960
The rain will start soon, and then there will be mud everywhere.

02:40.960 --> 02:42.960
We must leave now.

02:42.960 --> 02:48.960
Manuel took down the tents, and Joe and Pedro put the boxes into the truck.

02:49.960 --> 02:51.960
Hurry, shouted Leon.

02:51.960 --> 02:57.960
It's 10 o'clock. Let's go.

02:57.960 --> 03:00.960
Soon, everything was in the truck.

03:00.960 --> 03:05.960
Joe sat in the driver's seat. Leon sat beside him.

03:05.960 --> 03:11.960
Manuel and Pedro climbed into the back of the truck.

03:11.960 --> 03:15.960
Joe started the engine, and the journey began.

03:16.960 --> 03:19.960
They drove easily for the first 20 kilometres.

03:19.960 --> 03:22.960
Then they came to a stream.

03:22.960 --> 03:26.960
There was no water here last week. Pedro shouted to Manuel.

03:26.960 --> 03:29.960
Look at the water now.

03:29.960 --> 03:32.960
The stream was full of water.

03:32.960 --> 03:37.960
Joe slowed down and drove the truck carefully through the rushing water.

03:37.960 --> 03:41.960
They crossed the stream, and Joe drove faster.

03:41.960 --> 03:44.960
The rain was now falling heavily.

03:44.960 --> 03:49.960
The truck was very muddy, and the truck began to slide.

03:49.960 --> 03:53.960
Watch out! Shouted Leon. But it was too late.

03:53.960 --> 03:59.960
The truck stopped. The wheels were still turning, but the truck was not moving.

03:59.960 --> 04:03.960
The wheels were turning round and round in the mud.

04:03.960 --> 04:07.960
Leon got out, and Pedro and Manuel jumped down.

04:07.960 --> 04:10.960
Joe sat in the driver's seat.

04:10.960 --> 04:13.960
Leon looked at the wheels in the mud.

04:13.960 --> 04:15.960
Then he looked up at Joe.

04:15.960 --> 04:18.960
It's your fault, he said angrily.

04:18.960 --> 04:23.960
You were driving too fast.

04:23.960 --> 04:27.960
Pedro, you cut branches from those trees, ordered Leon.

04:27.960 --> 04:31.960
And you, Manuel, throw the branches under the wheels.

04:31.960 --> 04:36.960
Pedro got a large knife out of the truck, and Manuel helped him.

04:36.960 --> 04:38.960
Leon turned to Joe.

04:38.960 --> 04:40.960
You, come and help us.

04:40.960 --> 04:42.960
Joe did not move.

04:42.960 --> 04:45.960
I'm driving the truck, he said.

04:45.960 --> 04:48.960
That's my job. I'm boss here.

04:48.960 --> 04:51.960
Shouted Leon. Come and help us.

04:51.960 --> 04:56.960
Joe did not say anything. He did not get out of the truck.

04:56.960 --> 05:01.960
Leon looked at him angrily. Then Leon walked away.

05:01.960 --> 05:05.960
Manuel and Pedro threw branches under the wheels.

05:05.960 --> 05:07.960
Okay, that's enough.

05:07.960 --> 05:10.960
Said Leon. Let's go.

05:11.960 --> 05:13.960
Joe started the engine again.

05:13.960 --> 05:16.960
Pedro and Manuel pushed the back of the truck.

05:16.960 --> 05:19.960
The wheels turned, and the engine roared.

05:19.960 --> 05:22.960
But the truck did not move.

05:22.960 --> 05:25.960
Push harder, shouted Leon.

05:25.960 --> 05:28.960
Suddenly, the truck moved forward.

05:28.960 --> 05:30.960
It was out of the mud.

05:30.960 --> 05:33.960
Pedro and Manuel shouted happily.

05:33.960 --> 05:37.960
At that moment, a large branch blew up from under a wheel.

05:37.960 --> 05:41.960
It hit Leon's arm. He stepped back and fell in the mud.

05:41.960 --> 05:43.960
Stopped the truck.

05:43.960 --> 05:46.960
Shouted Manuel. Leon's hurt.

05:49.960 --> 05:52.960
My arm. Let me see.

05:52.960 --> 05:56.960
It hurts. It's broken.

05:58.960 --> 06:00.960
I'll tie it up.

06:01.960 --> 06:03.960
That's better. Thanks.

06:03.960 --> 06:06.960
You're lucky it's your left arm.

06:06.960 --> 06:09.960
Yes. I can use my right.

06:15.960 --> 06:18.960
At midday, it was still raining heavily.

06:18.960 --> 06:20.960
The track was covered with mud.

06:20.960 --> 06:24.960
Joe drove slowly, and the truck did not stop again.

06:24.960 --> 06:27.960
They climbed up a steep hill.

06:27.960 --> 06:30.960
On the other side, the track went down to a river.

06:30.960 --> 06:33.960
It was the biggest river in the forest.

06:33.960 --> 06:37.960
This was the last river between the men and their base.

06:37.960 --> 06:40.960
An old wooden bridge crossed over the river.

06:40.960 --> 06:43.960
They drove down towards the bridge.

06:43.960 --> 06:46.960
Look. Leon shouted to Joe.

06:46.960 --> 06:50.960
Something's wrong. It's the bridge. It's broken.

06:50.960 --> 06:52.960
Joe did not stop the truck.

06:52.960 --> 06:55.960
He drove down slowly to the bank of the river.

06:55.960 --> 06:58.960
He drove to the edge of the broken bridge.

06:58.960 --> 07:00.960
Then he stopped.

07:03.960 --> 07:06.960
They all got out of the truck.

07:06.960 --> 07:10.960
They stood in silence. Nobody spoke.

07:10.960 --> 07:14.960
They looked at the broken bridge and at the rushing water.

07:14.960 --> 07:16.960
Pedro spoke first.

07:16.960 --> 07:19.960
There is no way across the river now.

07:19.960 --> 07:22.960
How can we get back to base?

07:22.960 --> 07:25.960
We must get help, said Leon.

07:25.960 --> 07:27.960
Pedro, you climb back up the hill.

07:27.960 --> 07:30.960
Take the radio with you and call base.

07:30.960 --> 07:35.960
Perhaps they'll hear you and send help.

07:35.960 --> 07:40.960
Manuel lifted the radio out of the truck and fixed it to Pedro's back.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.960
Joe stopped them.

07:42.960 --> 07:44.960
It won't work, he said.

07:44.960 --> 07:47.960
Why not? asked Leon.

07:47.960 --> 07:50.960
It isn't a strong radio, replied Joe.

07:50.960 --> 07:52.960
We're too far away from the base.

07:52.960 --> 07:55.960
No one will hear us from this side of the river.

07:55.960 --> 07:58.960
We must cross the river by ourselves.

07:58.960 --> 08:01.960
We can't, said Leon. We must get help.

08:01.960 --> 08:05.960
We can't get help from here, said Joe.

08:05.960 --> 08:07.960
We must cross the river first.

08:07.960 --> 08:09.960
Then we can get help.

08:09.960 --> 08:12.960
But how do we get across, asked Leon?

08:12.960 --> 08:15.960
It's too dangerous. Look at the water.

08:15.960 --> 08:20.960
The rain was still falling heavily and the water was rising.

08:20.960 --> 08:23.960
I have a plan, said Joe.

08:23.960 --> 08:26.960
Leon looked at Joe and smiled.

08:26.960 --> 08:29.960
You're clever, Joe, Leon said.

08:29.960 --> 08:32.960
You always have plans, but they never work.

08:32.960 --> 08:36.960
Let's listen to Joe's plan, said Manuel.

08:36.960 --> 08:40.960
We can use the boat, said Joe.

08:40.960 --> 08:41.960
Leon laughed.

08:41.960 --> 08:45.960
Don't be stupid, the boat's too small for four people,

08:45.960 --> 08:47.960
and look at the rushing water.

08:47.960 --> 08:49.960
It will carry the boat away.

08:49.960 --> 08:51.960
But we've got a rope, said Joe.

08:51.960 --> 08:54.960
We can tie the rope to the boat.

08:54.960 --> 08:57.960
But look, the water will carry the boat to the other side.

08:57.960 --> 09:00.960
We can try it, said Pedro.

09:00.960 --> 09:03.960
It won't work, said Leon.

09:03.960 --> 09:06.960
It will work, said Joe.

09:06.960 --> 09:09.960
Look, I'll show you.

09:09.960 --> 09:14.960
We tie a rope to this end of the bridge.

09:14.960 --> 09:20.960
Then we tie the rope to the boat and carry it up the river.

09:20.960 --> 09:25.960
Two of us get into the boat and push it into the river.

09:25.960 --> 09:30.960
We paddle hard to get to the other side.

09:30.960 --> 09:35.960
We tie the rope to the other end of the bridge.

09:35.960 --> 09:40.960
One of us pulls the rope and brings the boat back.

09:40.960 --> 09:45.960
It won't work, Leon said, but we can try it.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.960
I'll go first, Joe said.

09:48.960 --> 09:50.960
It's my plan.

09:50.960 --> 09:53.960
No, let me go, said Pedro.

09:53.960 --> 09:55.960
I am stronger.

09:55.960 --> 09:58.960
You can both go, said Leon.

09:58.960 --> 10:01.960
Pedro, you stay on the other side.

10:01.960 --> 10:05.960
Joe, you bring the boat back, and then you can take Manuel.

10:05.960 --> 10:08.960
Then you can come back again for me.

10:08.960 --> 10:10.960
Good, Joe said.

10:10.960 --> 10:12.960
Pedro, you bring the radio.

10:12.960 --> 10:15.960
You can use it on the other side of the river.

10:15.960 --> 10:19.960
Pedro got the rubber boat out of the truck and pumped it up.

10:19.960 --> 10:22.960
Leon helped him with his right arm.

10:22.960 --> 10:25.960
There was a long rope in the back of the truck.

10:25.960 --> 10:28.960
Joe tied it to the broken bridge.

10:28.960 --> 10:33.960
Manuel tied the other end of the rope to the rubber boat.

10:33.960 --> 10:35.960
It's a long rope, Leon said.

10:35.960 --> 10:37.960
It'll be all right.

10:38.960 --> 10:40.960
Hurry, said Joe.

10:40.960 --> 10:45.960
The water is rising quickly.

10:45.960 --> 10:48.960
Joe and Pedro carried the boat.

10:48.960 --> 10:51.960
Manuel and Leon walked behind them.

10:51.960 --> 10:53.960
Manuel held the boat.

10:53.960 --> 10:57.960
Joe and Pedro climbed in.

10:57.960 --> 11:02.960
The rushing water took the boat into the middle of the river.

11:02.960 --> 11:05.960
The boat crossed to the other side.

11:06.960 --> 11:08.960
Joe held on.

11:08.960 --> 11:13.960
Pedro climbed out of the boat.

11:13.960 --> 11:18.960
Pedro tied the rope to a piece of the bridge.

11:18.960 --> 11:22.960
Pedro stayed on the far side of the river.

11:22.960 --> 11:28.960
Joe pulled hard on the rope and the boat slowly came back to Leon and Manuel.

11:28.960 --> 11:31.960
You get in now, Manuel, said Leon.

11:31.960 --> 11:33.960
I'm going last.

11:33.960 --> 11:36.960
No, you're not, Manuel replied.

11:36.960 --> 11:38.960
Your arm is broken.

11:38.960 --> 11:40.960
You can't get into the boat alone.

11:40.960 --> 11:41.960
You need help.

11:41.960 --> 11:43.960
I'll help you.

11:43.960 --> 11:46.960
Manuel is right, said Joe.

11:46.960 --> 11:48.960
You need help, Leon.

11:48.960 --> 11:51.960
Manuel helped Leon into the boat.

11:51.960 --> 11:56.960
He sat down in the boat and Joe pulled hard on the rope.

11:56.960 --> 11:59.960
Trouble came suddenly.

11:59.960 --> 12:02.960
Joe and Leon were in the middle of the river.

12:02.960 --> 12:04.960
Leon saw the tree first.

12:04.960 --> 12:07.960
The rushing water was pulling it down the river.

12:07.960 --> 12:10.960
Look out, Leon shouted.

12:10.960 --> 12:12.960
Joe looked round.

12:12.960 --> 12:16.960
At that moment, the branches of the tree hit the boat.

12:16.960 --> 12:18.960
Joe held onto the rope.

12:18.960 --> 12:22.960
His feet slipped and the boat moved away from him.

12:22.960 --> 12:25.960
Hold onto the rope, Leon shouted.

12:25.960 --> 12:27.960
But Joe did not listen.

12:27.960 --> 12:33.960
He let go of the rope and swam towards the rubber boat.

12:33.960 --> 12:37.960
Joe was a good swimmer and he soon reached the boat.

12:37.960 --> 12:41.960
He held it tightly and kicked his legs hard in the water.

12:41.960 --> 12:44.960
The boat moved away from the tree.

12:44.960 --> 12:47.960
Good, Joe shouted to Leon.

12:47.960 --> 12:49.960
The boat's free.

12:49.960 --> 12:52.960
Leave the boat, shouted Leon.

12:52.960 --> 12:54.960
Save yourself.

12:54.960 --> 12:56.960
Joe did not listen.

12:56.960 --> 12:59.960
Joe held the boat and kicked his legs.

12:59.960 --> 13:03.960
A few moments later, Joe heard a loud noise.

13:03.960 --> 13:05.960
What's that?

13:05.960 --> 13:07.960
He asked Leon.

13:07.960 --> 13:10.960
It's a waterfall, replied Leon.

13:10.960 --> 13:12.960
The water will pull the boat over.

13:12.960 --> 13:15.960
Leave the boat, save yourself.

13:15.960 --> 13:16.960
Look.

13:16.960 --> 13:18.960
Shouted Joe.

13:18.960 --> 13:20.960
There's a rock in front of us.

13:20.960 --> 13:22.960
We must reach it.

13:22.960 --> 13:25.960
Don't be a fool, said Leon.

13:25.960 --> 13:26.960
Leave yourself.

13:26.960 --> 13:28.960
You can't save me.

13:28.960 --> 13:31.960
The water rushed round the boat.

13:31.960 --> 13:34.960
It was pulling them towards the waterfall.

13:34.960 --> 13:36.960
Joe kicked his legs harder.

13:36.960 --> 13:39.960
The boat moved quickly towards the rock.

13:39.960 --> 13:40.960
Get ready.

13:40.960 --> 13:41.960
Shouted Joe.

13:41.960 --> 13:43.960
Jump for the rock.

13:43.960 --> 13:46.960
Leon was ready.

13:46.960 --> 13:51.960
The boat came near the rock and Leon jumped.

13:51.960 --> 13:55.960
Joe let go of the boat and swam to the rock.

13:55.960 --> 13:57.960
The two men lay on the rock.

13:57.960 --> 14:01.960
For a few minutes, they did not say anything.

14:01.960 --> 14:05.960
Then Leon turned and smiled at Joe.

14:05.960 --> 14:08.960
Joe had saved his life.

14:08.960 --> 14:10.960
We're not safe yet.

14:10.960 --> 14:11.960
Joe shouted.

14:11.960 --> 14:14.960
The rain has stopped, but the water is still rising.

14:14.960 --> 14:17.960
It'll cover the rock in an hour or two.

14:17.960 --> 14:19.960
Joe was right.

14:19.960 --> 14:22.960
There was water all round the two men.

14:22.960 --> 14:25.960
In front of them, the water dropped over the waterfall.

14:25.960 --> 14:28.960
Behind them, there was the broken bridge.

14:28.960 --> 14:31.960
We must get help, said Leon.

14:31.960 --> 14:33.960
But how?

14:33.960 --> 14:35.960
Pedro, replied Joe.

14:35.960 --> 14:38.960
He can help us. He's got the radio.

14:44.960 --> 14:47.960
Pedro was waiting on the far side of the river.

14:47.960 --> 14:49.960
He watched Joe and Leon.

14:49.960 --> 14:51.960
They climbed onto the rock.

14:51.960 --> 14:53.960
They were safe.

14:53.960 --> 14:56.960
They want to be safe for long, thought Pedro.

14:56.960 --> 14:59.960
I must call base and get help.

14:59.960 --> 15:02.960
Pedro climbed up the hill behind him.

15:02.960 --> 15:05.960
He walked quickly for half an hour.

15:05.960 --> 15:09.960
At the top of the hill, he climbed onto a high rock.

15:09.960 --> 15:13.960
He took the radio off his back and pulled out the aerial.

15:13.960 --> 15:16.960
Pedro spoke into the radio.

15:16.960 --> 15:18.960
PX-75 calling base.

15:18.960 --> 15:22.960
PX-75 calling base.

15:22.960 --> 15:24.960
He waited and listened.

15:24.960 --> 15:27.960
PX-75 calling base.

15:27.960 --> 15:30.960
PX-75 calling base.

15:30.960 --> 15:32.960
There was no reply.

15:32.960 --> 15:35.960
PX-75 calling base.

15:35.960 --> 15:38.960
PX-75 calling base.

15:42.960 --> 15:45.960
Philip was sitting at the control desk.

15:45.960 --> 15:47.960
He was listening to the radio.

15:47.960 --> 15:50.960
PX-75 was Leon's number.

15:50.960 --> 15:53.960
Philip turned the dials of the radio.

15:53.960 --> 15:55.960
The voice became clearer.

15:55.960 --> 15:59.960
Hello PX-75, said Philip.

15:59.960 --> 16:03.960
This is base. What's your message over?

16:03.960 --> 16:06.960
Hello base. PX-75 here.

16:06.960 --> 16:10.960
Pedro speaking. Can you hear me?

16:10.960 --> 16:14.960
Loud and clear Pedro. What's your message over?

16:14.960 --> 16:17.960
We're in trouble, said Pedro.

16:17.960 --> 16:21.960
The bridge over the river Sandano is broken.

16:21.960 --> 16:25.960
Joe and Leon are on a rock in the middle of the river.

16:25.960 --> 16:27.960
They are above the waterfall.

16:27.960 --> 16:30.960
Can you send help? Over.

16:30.960 --> 16:34.960
River Sandano, near bridge, above waterfall.

16:34.960 --> 16:38.960
Okay Pedro, help is coming. Over.

16:39.960 --> 16:43.960
Pedro climbed down the hill to the broken bridge.

16:43.960 --> 16:47.960
Manuel was waiting on the other side of the river.

16:47.960 --> 16:51.960
Pedro shouted and Manuel waved.

16:51.960 --> 16:54.960
Both men looked down the river.

16:54.960 --> 16:58.960
The water was rising fast and the rock looked very small now.

16:58.960 --> 17:02.960
On the rock, Joe was holding Leon in his arms.

17:02.960 --> 17:05.960
Leon's arm was covered in blood.

17:05.960 --> 17:09.960
His eyes were closed and he did not move.

17:09.960 --> 17:13.960
Then Joe heard the noise. A helicopter.

17:13.960 --> 17:16.960
It was high above the broken bridge.

17:16.960 --> 17:21.960
A helicopter! Joe shouted. Leon! Look!

17:21.960 --> 17:25.960
Leon's eyes were closed and he said nothing.

17:25.960 --> 17:28.960
The helicopter was soon over the rock.

17:28.960 --> 17:31.960
A rope was lowered and Joe held it.

17:31.960 --> 17:34.960
Then he tied it round Leon.

17:34.960 --> 17:39.960
Joe held Leon with one hand and he held the rope with the other.

17:39.960 --> 17:44.960
Slowly the two men were lifted in the air.

17:50.960 --> 17:55.960
Leon woke up slowly. He was still half asleep.

17:55.960 --> 17:58.960
Where am I? He asked.

17:58.960 --> 18:03.960
Then he remembered the rock and the helicopter and Joe.

18:03.960 --> 18:07.960
Joe! He shouted out. Where's Joe?

18:07.960 --> 18:11.960
Don't worry, said a voice. I'm not dead yet.

18:11.960 --> 18:15.960
Leon opened his eyes fully and saw Joe.

18:15.960 --> 18:21.960
Joe was smiling. Pedro and Manuel were standing next to him.

18:21.960 --> 18:24.960
The four men were in a hotted base.

18:24.960 --> 18:28.960
Leon was lying in bed and his arm was in plaster.

18:29.960 --> 18:33.960
You'll feel better in a few days Leon, said Joe.

18:33.960 --> 18:38.960
I feel better now, said Leon, but I need a drink.

18:38.960 --> 18:41.960
Water? Asked Manuel.

18:41.960 --> 18:44.960
No, not water, replied Leon.

18:44.960 --> 18:48.960
I don't want to see water again, not for a long time.

18:48.960 --> 18:51.960
And they all laughed.

18:59.960 --> 19:02.960
Dangerous Journey was read by Stephen Pacey

19:02.960 --> 19:08.960
and the recording produced by James Richardson at Studio AVP London.

